{{Sculpture | image = PL Adam Mickiewicz monument in Gorzów Wielkopolski 11.jpg | title = Monument of [[Adam Mickiewicz]] | artist = [[Józef Gosławski (Polish sculptor)|Józef Gosławski]] | year = 1957 | city = [[File:Flag of Poland.svg|20px]] [[Poland]], [[Gorzów Wielkopolski]] | museum = }} The '''Adam Mickiewicz monument in Gorzów Wielkopolski''' is a notable [[Gorzów Wielkopolski]] statue, located near a cross of [[Lwów Eaglets]] Street and [[Władysław Sikorski]] Street. The monument was designed by [[Józef Gosławski (Polish sculptor)|Józef Gosławski]]. The statue was unveiled 15 December 1957 to commemorate an anniversary of poet's death. The cast was produced by the ''Mechanical Plants "Gorzów"'' ([[Polish language|Polish]]: ''Zakłady Mechaniczne "Gorzów"''). Funds for monument came from contributions of local society.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ziemialubuska.pl/1930,1881,,.html|title=Gorzów Wlkp. - Wojcieszyce|last1=|first1=|date=|publisher=ziemialubuska.pl|language=pl|accessdate=2010-03-08}}</ref> In the original version [[Adam Mickiewicz]] held a feather in his left and a book in his right hand, but during the work a committee changed an idea and as a result one hand of the poet is 20&nbsp;cm longer than the other.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gorzow.gazeta.pl/gorzow/1,78945,5971869,Pomnikowa_anarchia__czyli_od_Micka_do_Marszalka.html|title=Pomnikowa anarchia, czyli od Micka do Marszałka|last1=Barański|first1=Dariusz|date=2008-11-20|publisher=gorzow.gazeta.pl|language=pl|accessdate=2010-03-08}}</ref>
