{{Infobox Newspaper | name = Berria | image = Berria.png | caption = | type = [[Daily newspaper]] | format = [[Broadsheet]] | owner = Euskal Editorea SL | founder = Euskarazko Komunikazio Taldea (EKT) (Now called '''Berria Taldea''') | publisher = Euskal Editorea SL | president = Beatriz Zabalondo | editor = Idurre Lazkano | generalmanager = Martxelo Otamendi | staff = Anjel Lertxundi, Angel Erro, Garbine Ubeda, Idurre Eskisabel | foundation = June 21, 2003 | political = [[Left-wing]] | language = [[Basque language|Basque]] | headquarters = Martin Ugalde kultur parkea (Gudarien etorbidea, 20140 Andoain.) | circulation = 20,000 - 25,000 daily | sister newspapers = HITZA | ISSN = 1696-5108 | website = {{URL|www.berria.eus}} | publishing_country = [[Basque Country (greater region)|Basque Country]] }}
'''''Berria''''' ([[Basque language|Basque]]: '''''News''''') is the only daily [[newspaper]] published wholly in the [[Basque language]] and which can be read in the entirety of the [[Basque Country (historical territory)|Basque country]]. It was created after the closure of the previous Basque language newspaper, ''[[Egunkaria]]'', by the [[Spain|Spanish]] government, after being accused of having ties with [[ETA (separatist group)|ETA]].<ref>[http://www.elmundo.es/papel/2003/02/26/espana/1345020.html Del Olmo se basa en documentos de ETA para relacionar a 'Egunkaria' con la banda terrorista]</ref> The newspaper shutdown was regarded by many as an attack on freedom of speech and the Basque language.<ref>[http://www.eitb24.com/new/en/m_not_40484/politics/Denunciation-act-on-second-anniversary-Basque-newspaper/ Denunciation act on second anniversary of Basque newspaper shutdown]</ref> After 7 years, in April 2010, the editorial team were found not guilty and acquitted.<ref>[http://www.publico.es/espana/305542/audiencia/nacional/abusleve/cinco/directivos/egunkaria La Audiencia Nacional absuelve a los cinco directivos de 'Egunkaria'] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100416160031/http://www.publico.es/espana/305542/audiencia/nacional/abusleve/cinco/directivos/egunkaria |date=April 16, 2010 }}, ''Público'', 12 de abril de 2010.</ref><ref>[http://imagenes.publico.es/resources/archivos/2010/4/12/1271070489553egunkaria.pdf Sentencia íntegra de la Audiencia Nacional sobre el caso ''Egunkaria''.]</ref>
''Berria'' is published daily, with the exception of Monday. The first issue was released on 21 June 2003. The newspaper's headquarters is in [[Andoain]], [[Gipuzkoa]], in the autonomous Basque region, [[Basque Country (autonomous community)|Euskadi]], in northern [[Spain]]. There are also centres in [[Vitoria-Gasteiz]], [[Pamplona]], [[Bilbao]] and [[Bayonne]].
