{{unreferenced|date=September 2013}} {{Infobox song contest entry | song = Candlelight | image = [[Image:Csézy, Hungary, Eurovision 2008, 2nd semifinal.jpg|250px]] | caption = | language = | languages = [[English language|English]], [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]] | artist = [[Csézy]] | with = Fool Moon | year = 2008 | country = Hungary | composer = Viktor Rakonczai | lyricist = Imre Mózsik | place = | points = | place_semi = 19th | points_semi = 6 | lyrics = [http://www.diggiloo.net/?2008hu from Diggiloo Thrush] | prev = Unsubstantial Blues | prev_link = Unsubstantial Blues | next = Dance With Me | next_link = Dance With Me (Zoli Ádok song) }}
'''"Candlelight"''' is a song performed by the [[Hungarian people|Hungarian]] singer [[Csézy]]. This song was chosen to represent [[Hungary]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2008]] in [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia]]. The Hungarian version of the song is called ''Szívverés'' (Heartbeat).
The song was written by Viktor Rakonczai who represented Hungary at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1997]] as a member of [[V.I.P. (Hungarian band)|V.I.P.]]
Csézy performed the song in the second Semi-final on 22 May 2008. It was performed fifteenth (following [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]]'s [[Diana Gurtskaya]] with ''[[Peace Will Come]]'' and preceding [[Malta]]'s [[Morena Camilleri|Morena]] with ''[[Vodka (song)|Vodka]]''). The song failed to secure a place in the final, finishing last with six points.
It was succeeded as Hungarian representative by "[[Dance With Me (Zoli Ádok song)|Dance With Me]]" performed by [[Zoli Ádok]].
