The '''flag of [[French Sudan]]''' was the [[Flag of France|French tricolour]], used by most French colonial possessions, with a black [[stick figure]] with arms raised, a so-called ''kanaga''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.khanacademy.org/humanities/art-africa/west-africa/mali1/a/mask-kanaga-dogon-peoples|title=Mask (Kanaga) (Dogon peoples)|website=Khan Academy|language=en|access-date=2018-11-12}}</ref>. The flag continued to be used when the colony gained autonomy from France in 1958, but its colors were changed to green, yellow and red with the adoption of the flag of the independent [[Mali Federation]] in 1959.

