'''Kuta''' is a handmade cloth many [[Eritrea]]n and [[Ethiopia]]n men use to cover their head and shoulders when they wear clothing made out of [[chiffon (clothing)|chiffon]], especially when attending church. It is made up of two layers of fabric, unlike [[gabi (clothing)|gabi]] which is made out of four. [[Netela]] or netsela is the female version.

