{{EngvarB|date=January 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}} {{Infobox Playboy Playmate <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox Playboy Playmate/doc]] --> | image = | imagesize = | caption = | name = Madeleine Collinson | issue = October 1970 | birth_name = | birth_place = [[Sliema]], [[Malta]] | birth_date = {{birth date|df=yes|1952|7|22}} | death_date = {{death date and age|df=yes|2014|8|14|1952|7|22}} | death_place = [[Msida]], Malta | bust = 34 in | waist = 22 in | hips = 35 in | height = 5 ft 6 in | weight = 110 lb | preceded = [[Debbie Ellison]] | succeeded = [[Avis Miller]] }}
'''Madeleine Collinson''' (22 July 1952 – 14 August 2014) was a [[Maltese people|Maltese]]-[[British people|British]] model and actress. She was chosen as ''[[Playboy]]'' magazine's [[Playboy Playmate|Playmate of the Month]] in October 1970, together with her twin sister [[Mary Collinson]]. They were the first [[identical twin]] Playmate sisters.
==Career== The Collinson twins first arrived in Britain in April 1969,<ref>{{cite book |first=Simon |last=Sheridan |title=Keeping the British End Up: Four Decades of Saucy Cinema |publisher=Reynolds & Hearn Books |edition=3rd |year=2007 |isbn=978-0-9529260-7-8}}</ref> and prior to their appearance in ''Playboy'' one of the first people to use them was the glamour photographer/film maker [[Harrison Marks]] who cast them as saucy maids in his short film ''Halfway Inn''. The film, made for the 8mm market, was shot sometime between their British arrival, and July 1970, when a still from the film was used in a Marks' advert that ran in that month's issue of ''Continental Film Review'' magazine.<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Halfway Inn |magazine=Continental Film Review |date=July 1970 |page=26}}</ref>
Both sisters went on to acting careers, mostly in B-movies. Madeleine married a British [[Royal Air Force]] officer and raised three children. She later moved back to Malta and was involved in cultural and educational activities there. In her final years, Madeleine Collinson lived in [[San Gwann]] [[Malta]]. After several months of illness, she died at [[Mater Dei Hospital]] in [[Msida]] on 14 August 2014 with her twin sister Mary present.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.starburstmagazine.com/movie-news/9466-madeleine-collinson-rip|title=Madeleine Collinson, R.I.P.|work=[[Starburst (magazine)|Starburst]]|date=16 August 2014|first=Martin|last=Unsworth|accessdate=6 September 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140906203610/http://www.starburstmagazine.com/movie-news/9466-madeleine-collinson-rip|archivedate=6 September 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/madeleine-collinson-playboy-centrefold-model-who-also-appeared-with-her-sister-mary-in-the-horror-9856981.html |title=Madeleine Collinson: Playboy centrefold model who also appeared with her sister Mary in the horror film Twins of Evil |first=Simon |last=Farquhar |authorlink=Simon Farquhar |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |date=November 12, 2014}}</ref>
==Filmography== * ''[[Come Back Peter|Some Like It Sexy]]'' (1969) * ''[[Permissive (film)|Permissive]] ''(1970) * ''[[Groupie Girl]]'' (1970) * ''[[She'll Follow You Anywhere]]'' (1971) * ''[[The Love Machine (film)|The Love Machine]]'' (1971) * ''[[Twins of Evil]]'' (aka ''Twins of [[Dracula]]'', 1971)
