{{italic title}}
'''''South-African Folk-Tales''''' is a book by [[James Honeÿ]] published in 1910.  It contains forty-four [[folklore|folk tales]] from [[South Africa]] (some of which are merely different versions of the same story), mostly from the [[San people|Bushmen]], although stories of the [[Khoikhoi]] and [[Zulu people|Zulu]] are also presented.

The stories are almost entirely non-religious in nature, and focus exclusively on [[Traditional African religion|animal stories]].

