{{Infobox company | name = TVTEL | logo = Tvtel.png | type = [[Private company|Private]] | industry = [[Telecommunication]] | fate = Merged with [[NOS (Portuguese media company)|ZON Multimédia]] | founded = [[Porto]], [[Portugal]] ({{Start date|1999}}) | defunct = {{End date|2009}} | products = [[Direct broadcast satellite]], [[cable television]] | homepage = [http://www.tvtel.pt/ tvtel.pt] }} '''TVTEL''' (TVTEL Comunicações, S.A.) was a [[Portugal|Portuguese]] [[digital television|digital]] satellite and cable [[Pay TV|pay television]] service provider. The satellite service started on June 26, 2007, and it was on the [[Eurobird 9]] satellite, broadcasting [[Free-to-air|FTA]] and [[Conax]]-encrypted channels for the entire Europe. It was bought by [[ZON Multimédia]] in early 2009 and subsequently closed by it by merging its operations with ZON in late 2009.
==Spor TV controversy== Around February 2007, [[Sport TV|SportTV]] stopped broadcasting to TVTEL subscribers, causing a major outcry. SportTV justified the move by stating that TVTEL hadn't already start broadcasting exclusively with digital encryption. TVTEL later placed a caption on the channel saying "A SportTV não deixa que a TVTEL cresca, por que será?" (''SportTV doesn't allow TVTEL to grow, how come?''). It is worth mentioning that SportTV is 50% owned by former competitor (then its new owner) [[TV Cabo|ZON TVCabo]].
This controversy was somewhat similar to that of [[Virgin Media]] vs [[BSkyB]].
